label: LBL_APITUBETHKNOTE1
en: For elastic design (fraction of time in rupture regime = 0), the maximum tube temperature equals input for temperature at maximum operating pressure.  For rupture design (fraction of time in rupture regime > 0), the maximum allowable continuous temperature at average pressure is based on actual thickness selected to give design life, but limited to Maximum Design Metal Temperature for selected tube material.
chs: 对于弹性设计（破裂状态下的时间分数=0），最大管子温度等于最大工作压力下的温度输入。 对于破裂设计（破裂状态下的时间分数>0），平均压力下的最大允许连续温度是基于为设计寿命而选择的实际厚度，但仅限于所选管子材料的最大设计金属温度。

label: LBL_APITUBETHKNOTE2
en: Maximum elastic design temperature is limited to stress curve intersection temperature.  If tube is operated above this temperature, then rupture design controls and the average pressure shall not exceed pressure shown in the rupture design.
chs: 最大的弹性设计温度被限制在应力曲线的交点温度。 如果管子在这个温度以上运行，那么破裂设计就会受到控制，平均压力不得超过破裂设计中显示的压力。

label: LBL_APITUBETHKNOTE3
en: The rupture analysis for a linear changing temperature profile is based on a lower limit of the start of run temperature and an upper limit of the end of run temperature. A tube operating continuously at the equivalent temperature will suffer the same creep damage as the one operating at the above linear profile.  Operation at a constant metal temperature above the equivalent temperature may result in a life shorter than the design life.
chs: 线性变化的温度曲线的断裂分析是基于运行开始温度的下限和运行结束温度的上限。 在等效温度下连续运行的管子将遭受与在上述线性剖面下运行的管子相同的蠕变损坏。 在高于等效温度的恒定金属温度下运行可能会导致寿命短于设计寿命。

label: LBL_APITUBETHKNOTE4
en: The rupture design is performed at a constant temperature equal to the equivalent temperature and the specified design life.
chs: 破裂设计是在等于等效温度和指定设计寿命的恒定温度下进行的。
